extends views/partials/main.pug

block content
    section(class="lg:pt-52 md:pt-32 py-16 flex flex-col items-center text-center")
        h1(class='lg:text-5xl text-3xl rainbow-text') This article has been deprecated.
        .my-8
        p Thank you to all the people who have read this article over the years, or to those who have linked to it - the amount of traffic was quite surprising.
        br
        p Unfortunately the solution no longer works reliably (due to updates from both Synology and Resolve. <b>Note: the article was almost <i>5 years old</i></b>).
        p I have therefore removed the article in its entirety. I apologize for any inconvenience this may cause.
        br
        p Should you still need to look at the old video, I have an unlisted version available here:
        .my-8
        <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/MqJuKu38BsA" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe>
        p If DSM borked up your Postgres again, you should be able to recover your data using the steps shown in this.
        .my-8
        br
        p
            = "If you are looking for a solution to run PostgreSQL on a Synology NAS, I recommend you look at "
            a(href='https://github.com/elliotmatson/Docker-Davinci-Resolve-Project-Server#synology' target='_blank' class="text-blue-200 hover:underline") this project by Elliot Matson on GitHub
            = " instead."
        p If your Synology supports virtual machines, using that docker container on any VM will be your best bet without too much tinkering.
        .my-8
        p I will leave this page up for a while, but it will eventually be removed.
